title: Drawing, "End Table, Round", early 20th century
medium: Graphite and green color pencil on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite
markings: Small stamp in red ink at lower right: DONALD DESKEY/ 145 WEST 57TH STREET/ NEW YORK CITY
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite at lower right corner: SCALE 1"=1'0"/#/6080 [circled]; lower right corner in red color pencil: P; dimensions in graphite.
description: Perspective, plan, and elevation drawing of round end table. Glass top of table, supported by tubular metal pedestal and four tubular legs. Cylindrical glass fish tank at center of table, built into structure.
